                                        "body": "The provisions of this code relating to the construction, <i><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/north_carolina/irc-2021/chapter/2/definitions#alteration_\">alteration</a></i>, <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/north_carolina/irc-2021/chapter/2/definitions#repair_\">repair</a>, enlargement, restoration, relocation or moving of buildings or structures shall not be mandatory for <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/north_carolina/irc-2021/chapter/2/definitions#building_existing_\">existing buildings</a> or structures identified and classified by the state or local <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/north_carolina/irc-2021/chapter/2/definitions#jurisdiction_\">jurisdiction</a> as <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/north_carolina/irc-2021/chapter/2/definitions#historic_building_\">historic buildings</a> where such buildings or structures are judged by the code official to be safe and in the public interest of health, safety and welfare regarding any proposed construction, <i><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/north_carolina/irc-2021/chapter/2/definitions#alteration_\">alteration</a></i>, <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/north_carolina/irc-2021/chapter/2/definitions#repair_\">repair</a>, enlargement, restoration, relocation or moving of buildings.",
